</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Salento</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="hatnote">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Salento_(disambiguation)" title="Salento (disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig">Salento (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Zona-Salento-Posizione.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Zona-Salento-Posizione.png/200px-Zona-Salento-Posizione.png" width="200" height="233" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3e/Zona-Salento-Posizione.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3e/Zona-Salento-Posizione.png 2x" data-file-width="269" data-file-height="313" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Zona-Salento-Posizione.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Salento.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Salento</b> (<i><b>Salentu</b></i> in <a href="/wiki/Salentino_dialect" title="Salentino dialect">Salentino dialect</a>) is the southeastern <a href="/wiki/Peninsula" title="Peninsula">peninsular</a> extension of the <a href="/wiki/Apulia" title="Apulia">Apulia</a> (Puglia) region into the <a href="/wiki/Mediterranean_Sea" title="Mediterranean Sea">Mediterranean Sea</a>, in southeastern-most <a href="/wiki/Italy" title="Italy">Italy</a>. It is a sub-<a href="/wiki/Peninsula" title="Peninsula">peninsula</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Italian_Peninsula" title="Italian Peninsula">Italian Peninsula</a>, sometimes described as the "heel" of the Italian "boot".</p>
<p>It encompasses the entire <a href="/wiki/Local_government" title="Local government">administrative</a> area of the <a href="/wiki/Province_of_Lecce" title="Province of Lecce">province of Lecce</a>, a large part of the <a href="/wiki/Province_of_Brindisi" title="Province of Brindisi">province of Brindisi</a> and part of that of <a href="/wiki/Province_of_Taranto" title="Province of Taranto">Taranto</a>.</p>
<p>The peninsula is also known as <a href="/wiki/Terra_d%27Otranto" title="Terra d'Otranto">Terra d'Otranto</a>, and in ancient times was called variously Messapia, Calabria, and Salentina.</p>
<p></p>
